      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>42</ID>
      <DefaultText>"The Memovira is doomed. The Bloom bonds with one person for a while, and then it devours them - it's all part of a feeding cycle, and her time has come."

{CRIT}</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>43</ID>
      <DefaultText>Grisseler's eyes light up with sudden understanding. "Twenty years in this place. Twenty long years, and I never seen it before, never seen it clear.  But you're right. She builds 'em up full of power and hate, then she eats 'em and chooses another to rule in their place."

His eyes grow wide. "That means *you're* the one..."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>44</ID>
      <DefaultText>Grisseler squints at you hard. "Think *you* know the Bloom better than *me*? You been here what? A few days? I been here twenty *years*, you arrogant little bastard! If she had any kind of 'cycle,' I of all people would know."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>46</ID>
      <DefaultText>His eyes widen with a sudden understanding. "*You're* the one, the one she's been whispering about." He lowers his slugspitter. "Damned if I didn't see it before."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>47</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You think you know the Bloom better than me? I been eaten by the Bloom three times, and I've crawled through her guts for twenty long years. If the Bloom's on anybody's side, it's mine!"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
